00:33:14.330 --> 00:33:15.830
Very simple.

00:33:15.830 --> 00:33:18.590
I'm going to need to
be extremely organized.

00:33:18.590 --> 00:33:21.170
I'm going to need to be very
good at knowing what to say yes

00:33:21.170 --> 00:33:24.120
to and what to say no to.

00:33:24.120 --> 00:33:27.815
I'm going to need to be very
good at looking after myself.

00:33:27.815 --> 00:33:30.650
What's my strategy for
keeping myself healthy--

00:33:30.650 --> 00:33:32.980
mentally, physically?

00:33:32.980 --> 00:33:36.530
All really specific,
very tangible skills,

00:33:36.530 --> 00:33:38.660
things that you
can be doing that

00:33:38.660 --> 00:33:42.810
make all the difference
in the battle for balance

00:33:42.810 --> 00:33:44.840
that require practice.

00:33:44.840 --> 00:33:48.710
They require you to
get good at them.

00:33:48.710 --> 00:33:52.830
And in the fourth and final
step in The Babyproof Method

00:33:52.830 --> 00:33:55.500
is perseverance.

00:33:55.500 --> 00:33:56.910
How do you persevere?

00:33:56.910 --> 00:34:00.090
How will you keep going?

00:34:00.090 --> 00:34:03.670
When, not if, when
you reach a point

00:34:03.670 --> 00:34:07.830
that you want to give up, when
things seem like they're too

00:34:07.830 --> 00:34:11.550
hard, that inevitable moment--

00:34:11.550 --> 00:34:13.989
Martin Luther
King, the 29th time

00:34:13.989 --> 00:34:18.219
