I've called it The
30:30 Challenge.

00:40:49.760 --> 00:40:51.050
Super easy.

00:40:51.050 --> 00:40:55.220
Whatever time you get up,
even if it is four o'clock,

00:40:55.220 --> 00:40:58.720
set your alarm to get
up 30 minutes earlier.

00:40:58.720 --> 00:41:00.630
But there are rules--

00:41:00.630 --> 00:41:02.140
no work.

00:41:02.140 --> 00:41:07.000
This is not a license to
extend your working day.

00:41:07.000 --> 00:41:09.490
That is worse than lying in
bed until the last minute

00:41:09.490 --> 00:41:11.680
and pressing snooze.

00:41:11.680 --> 00:41:16.810
No one, no devices, no news.

00:41:19.390 --> 00:41:23.940
Sounds so simple,
very hard to do.

00:41:23.940 --> 00:41:25.750
But it's a skill.

00:41:25.750 --> 00:41:27.460
Practice.

00:41:27.460 --> 00:41:32.200
30 minutes earlier for 30
days, the next 30 days.

00:41:32.200 --> 00:41:33.850
This is my challenge to you.

00:41:36.720 --> 00:41:39.910
What will you do with that time?

00:41:39.910 --> 00:41:42.000
Look at the big picture.

00:41:42.000 --> 00:41:45.600
Think about the week
you've got coming up.

00:41:45.600 --> 00:41:48.494
What's working,
what isn't working?

00:41:48.494 --> 00:41:49.410
What could you change?

00:41:49.410 --> 00:41:51.866
What could you do differently?

00:41:51.866 --> 00:41:56.560
Controllables every
step of the way.

00:41:56.560 --> 00:41:59.370
Good luck and let
me know how it goes.

